Info English:

A failed playwright, Henry Harrison, develops an odd mentor relationship 
with Louis Ives, a troubled, cross-dressing, aspiring writer to whom Henry 
sublets a room in his New York apartment. Henry teaches Louis the art of 
being an "extra man," accompanying and entertaining wealthy older women in 
their fanciful social lives. Along the way, Louis encounters an 
environmentally conscious co-worker, Mary Powell, and a jealous, eccentric 
neighbor, Gershon.
